US&nbsp;50 crosses the central portion of Nevada, entering the west side of the state near Lake Tahoe and exiting the east side near Great Basin National Park. The route crosses mostly desolate terrain in the journey across the state; US&nbsp;50 passes through several large desert valleys and Drainage basin basins. The highway crosses 17 named mountain passes that break up the Nevada desert. To crest of some of the passes along US&nbsp;50 requires navigating steep 8% Grade slope grades and hairpin turns through Temperate coniferous forest pine forests to reach altitudes of over convert 7000 ft m sigfig=2. 
